@endnode

@node 1_1__07_06_2026_ "1.1 (07.06.2026)"
@{b}1.1 (07.06.2026)@{ub}

@{b}Partition Table library@{ub}

  * @{b}Cold-boot RDB partition scanner@{ub} , extracted from @{fg shine}compactflash.device@{fg text} : the RDB
    autoboot @{fg shine}RTF_COLDSTART@{fg text} hook, the filesystem-handler loader, and the hunk
    relocator.
  * @{b}Duplicate RDB drive names are made unique at cold boot.@{ub} When two cards carry
    RDBs that reuse the same partition name (for example both define @{fg shine}DH0@{fg text} ), a
    clashing name now gets a numeric suffix ( @{fg shine}DH0.1@{fg text} , @{fg shine}DH0.2@{fg text} , ...).
  * Loads filesystem handlers stored in a compacted format ( @{fg shine}RELOC32SHORT@{fg text}
    relocations).
  * A partition with a damaged RDB entry is skipped instead of mounted (a @{fg shine}DosEnvec@{fg text}
    shorter than the @{fg shine}DOSTYPE@{fg text} field).
  * Filesystem handlers loaded from a card's RDB now appear in @{fg shine}FileSystem.resource@{fg text}
    under their own name instead of @{fg shine}ptable.library@{fg text} .

----------------------------------------
